                "title": "Appending 이/가 to a noun denotes the subject of the sentence.",
                "details": "When the noun ends in a consonant, the ending 이 is used. When the noun ends in a vowel, 가 is used. The subject particle is used to indicate the subject of the sentence. This is a more general usage than the topic particle (which is used more specifically)."
